msgid "Identity Brokering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "An Identity Broker is an intermediary service that connects multiple service providers with different identity providers.\n"
"As an intermediary service, the identity broker is responsible for creating\n"
"a trust relationship with an external identity provider in order to use its identities to access internal services exposed by service providers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "From a user perspective, an identity broker provides a user-centric and centralized way to manage identities across different security\n"
"domains or realms. An existing account can be linked with one or more identities from different identity providers or even created\n"
"based on the identity information obtained from them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "An identity provider is usually based on a specific protocol that is used to authenticate and communicate authentication and authorization information to their users.\n"
"It can be a social provider such as Facebook, Google or Twitter.  It can be a business partner whose users need to access your services. Or it an be a cloud-based identity\n"
"service that you want to integrate with.\n"
msgstr ""

